{{Quote|After more than two decades, the galaxy's most devastating war ended with the muted scratch of a writing stylus.|[[Historical Council]] of the Galactic Federation of Free Alliances|<ref name="The New Essential Chronology">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref>}}
The '''Pellaeon&ndash;Gavrisom Treaty''' was a [[Timeline of galactic history/Legends|significant]] treaty between the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] and the [[Imperial Remnant]] in [[19 ABY/Legends|19 ABY]]. Its signing effectively formalized the end of the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] and permitted peaceful coexistence between the New Republic and Imperial Remnant. The New Republic's [[Chief of State (New Republic)/Legends|Chief of State]] [[Ponc Gavrisom]] and the Imperial Remnant's [[Supreme Commander (Galactic Empire)/Legends|Supreme Commander]] [[Fleet Admiral/Legends|Fleet Admiral]] [[Gilad Pellaeon/Legends|Gilad Pellaeon]] signed the treaty, with [[Mon Mothma/Legends|Mon Mothma]] notable in attendance.

The Imperial Remnant had been driven back to the the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]] by the New Republic, after five relatively peaceful years, which purposed the cessation of hostilities, resulting in the ending of conflict between the Republic and Remnant, and opening up trade and commerce with both states and putting forth limitations on smuggling, while permitting [[Star system/Legends|systems]] in each side to choose their alignment.

==History==
===Early peace proposals===
{{Quote|A truce? Are you mad? The Moffs would rebel!|[[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Gilad Pellaeon/Legends|Gilad Pellaeon]] to [[Feena D'Asta]]|<ref name="Crimson Empire III: Empire Lost 2">[[Crimson Empire III: Empire Lost 2|''Crimson Empire III: Empire Lost'' 2]]</ref>}}
In the years following the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] forces engaged in several temporary, localized alliances against mutual threats. [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]] saw the [[Bakura Truce]] against the [[Ssi-ruu]]k<ref name="The Truce at Bakura">''[[The Truce at Bakura]]''</ref> and the [[Battle of Saijo]] against the [[Tof/Legends|Tofs]],<ref name="Star Wars 1977 107">[[Star Wars (1977) 107|''Star Wars'' (1977) 107]]</ref> and [[7 ABY/Legends|7 ABY]] saw the [[Battle of Vahaba]] against the forces of [[Zsinj]].<ref name="X-Wing: Solo Command">''[[X-Wing: Solo Command]]''</ref>

The first tentative plan for comprehensive peace between the New Republic and Imperial Remnant was proposed by Imperial Admiral [[Betl Oxtroe]] to the [[New Republic Provisional Council]] in 7 ABY. Oxtroe's proposal would appoint [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine's]] 11-year old grand-niece [[Ederlathh Pallopides/Legends|Ederlathh Pallopides]] as the titular Empress, with the former New Republic councilors holding effective power. Although the New Republic was eager to negotiate, the secret talks soon ended when Oxtroe was assassinated, apparently by [[Noghri/Legends|Noghri]] under the direction of [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn]].<ref name="Dark Empire Sourcebook">''[[Dark Empire Sourcebook]]''</ref>

A truce between the Imperial Remnant and the New Republic was also proposed to Pellaeon in [[13 ABY/Legends|13 ABY]] by [[Baron/Legends|Baron]] [[Ragez D'Asta]] and his daughter, [[Feena D'Asta]], as the cost of their bringing the [[D'Astan sector/Legends|D'Astan sector]] back into the Empire.<ref name="Crimson Empire III: Empire Lost 2" /> Pellaeon dispatched Feena D'Asta and [[Zam Basdor]] to negotiate with [[Mirith Sinn]] and [[Kir Kanos]] of the New Republic, but the meeting was [[Ambush at the peace negotiations|disrupted]] by the [[Restored Empire]] faction who succeeded in killing D'Asta.<ref name="Crimson Empire III: Empire Lost 5">[[Crimson Empire III: Empire Lost 5|''Crimson Empire III: Empire Lost'' 5]]</ref>

===End of the war===
{{Quote|It's time to send an emissary to the New Republic. To discuss the terms of our surrender.|[[Fleet Admiral/Legends|Fleet Admiral]] [[Gilad Pellaeon/Legends|Gilad Pellaeon]] to [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Ardiff]]|<ref name="SotP">''[[Specter of the Past]]''</ref>}}
In [[17 ABY/Legends|17 ABY]], after five relatively peaceful years, Imperial systems near the [[Hydian Way/Legends|Hydian Way]] began to suggest the cessation of hostilities. The [[New Republic Senate/Legends|New Republic Senate]] was favorable and proposed an [[New Republic amnesty bill|amnesty for former Imperials within the Republic]] as a peace overture. Fearing an invasion, the [[Council of Moffs/Legends|Council of Moffs]] secretly contacted [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Natasi Daala]], who had unified the [[replacement warlord]]s, and proposed a campaign against the New Republic. The [[Imperial Skirmishes|campaign]] was disastrous for the [[Imperial Military/Legends|Imperial Military]] and the [[Imperial Space]] was reduced to eight remote [[Sector/Legends|sectors]] in the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]].<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref><ref name="EGW" />

[[File:HandofThrawnEC.jpg|thumb|left|The Sinister Triumvirate.]]

The final treaty was the brainchild of Pellaeon who, after acknowledging the impossibility of an honorable victory over the New Republic, proposed it to the Council of Moffs, select officers of the [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Imperial Starfleet]], and other officials who, for the most part, grudgingly agreed.<ref name="EGW" /> [[Vilim Disra]], [[Moff/Legends|Moff]] of the [[Braxant sector/Legends|Braxant sector]], though openly siding with Pellaeon, chose to side with [[Emperor's Royal Guard/Legends|Imperial Guardsman]] [[Grodin Tierce (clone)|Grodin Tierce]] and a con-artist named [[Flim (Human)|Flim]] to take advantage of the [[Caamas Document Crisis]] in order to nearly bring both the Republic and the Empire into separate internal civil wars.<ref name="SotP" />

Pellaeon and [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]] engaged in preliminary talks aboard the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']] in the [[Pesitiin system/Legends|Pesitiin system]] before Pellaeon returned to Bastion. Fifteen days after Disra was detained by Pellaeon at Bastion, Gavrisom and Pellaeon signed the treaty aboard the [[Imperial I-class Star Destroyer|''Imperial I''-class Star Destroyer]] [[Chimaera/Legends|''Chimaera'']].<ref name="Vision of the Future" />

==Terms of the treaty==
[[File:Pellaeon-Gavrisom_Treaty1.jpg|thumb|right|The signature of the treaty.]]
The treaty put an end to the Galactic Civil War and opened the Imperial Remnant to trade and commerce with the New Republic. Additionally, it put forth limitations on smuggling for both governments to enforce. In addition, systems in either faction would be allowed to choose their alignment.<ref name="Vision of the Future" /> The treaty also banned the use of [[Cloaking device/Legends|cloaking devices]].<ref name="EGW" />

